# Documentation Patterns

## Documentation Structure
- **Development**: [DEVELOPMENT.md](mdc:docs/DEVELOPMENT.md)
- **Quality Standards**: [QUALITY_STANDARDS.md](mdc:docs/QUALITY_STANDARDS.md)
- **Architecture**: [ARCHITECTURE.md](mdc:docs/ARCHITECTURE.md)
- **Performance**: [PERFORMANCE_GUIDE.md](mdc:docs/PERFORMANCE_GUIDE.md)

## Markdown Standards
- **Pattern**: Clear headings, code examples, cross-references
- **Reference**: [Quality Standards Guide](mdc:docs/QUALITY_STANDARDS.md#documentation-standards)

## Docstring Format
- **Pattern**: Google-style docstrings
- **Reference**: [Quality Standards Guide](mdc:docs/QUALITY_STANDARDS.md#documentation-standards)

## Code Examples
- **Pattern**: Realistic examples from codebase
- **Reference**: [Quality Standards Guide](mdc:docs/QUALITY_STANDARDS.md#documentation-standards)

## API Documentation
- **Pattern**: Document all public functions and classes
- **Reference**: [Quality Standards Guide](mdc:docs/QUALITY_STANDARDS.md#documentation-standards)

## Maintenance
- **Pattern**: Keep documentation in sync with code
- **Reference**: [Quality Standards Guide](mdc:docs/QUALITY_STANDARDS.md#documentation-standards)
